benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/tags - Remove tags from invoice item

covered: Valid Deletion: TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC06, TC07, TC18 cover successful removal under various conditions.
Non-Existent Resource: TC08 (invoice item not found) -> 404.
Edge cases for tagDef values: malformed UUIDs (TC13), partial inputs (TC16), very large lists (TC14).
Error handling for bad inputs: malformed tagDef (TC13), XSS/injection in headers (TC15) -> 400/422.
Extra/unexpected query parameters are ignored and only specified tags affected (TC07).
Regression test for special characters in comment (TC18).
Accessibility: API docs and error messages readability (TC20).
gaps: Soft deletes: No tests verifying whether deletion clears tags only or marks the invoice item as deleted (soft delete semantics).
Explicit race-condition checks: No dedicated test asserting correctness under true race conditions beyond the general concurrency test (TC17).
Rate limiting: No tests for throttling or rate-limiting behavior.
Caching behavior: No tests verifying caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) for delete responses (applicable mainly to GET).
recommendations: Add a dedicated race-condition test to validate concurrent deletions on the same invoice item.
Add rate-limiting tests to verify the endpoints behavior under high request rates.
Consider adding tests for caching semantics or confirm that delete responses do not expose caching headers if not applicable.
Add tests for soft-delete semantics and audit/logging impact if relevant for the API design.
Expand authorization tests to cover forbidden/RBAC scenarios (e.g., 403) for insufficient permissions.
